                                            BCB bans 13 rebel cricketers  Dhaka: Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) on Wednesday hit back at 13 lsquo;rebel rsquo; players, banning them for 10 years for their decision to join the unofficial Indian Cricket League (ICL).  ldquo;The BCB has decided to ban for 10 years any player, official, or technical staff, who participates in events not authorised by it or the ICC, rdquo; a BCB spokesperson said.
  ldquo;The BCB has also barred them all from its domestic and international games and will not allow them access to any of its facilities. These decisions were taken at an emergency meeting on Wednesday and are in line with the ICC rsquo;s policy on unauthorised cricket, rdquo; he said.  T20 tourney  Karachi: Pakistan will meet hosts Canada while Sri Lanka will take on Zimbabwe in the opening round of an inaugural four-nation Twenty20 tournament in Toronto. The tournament is scheduled to be held from October 10-13.  Enamul in Ranji  Dhaka: Left-arm spinner Enamul Haque (Jr) has signed a contract to play for Maharashtra in the forthcoming Ranji Trophy.   Saina out  New Delhi: Saina Nehwal crashed out of the Japan Super series Badminton meet with a straight-game defeat in the Round I in Tokyo on Wednesday. Meanwhile, Andhra Pradesh chief minister Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy on Wednesday sanctioned a Rs 20 lakh cash award for Saina for winning the title in Chinese Taipei.  Pankaj wins  Chennai: Advani progressed to the pre-quarter finals while Ashok Shandilya started his campaign on a solid note in the Alliance Group-ASCA All India Invitational Snooker Tournament on Wednesday.   United contest  Calcutta: The lsquo;Extreme Manchester United Fan rsquo; contest in India was announced on Thursday during the launch of the Manchester United away jersey and the third jersey to celebrate the 40th anniversary of the club rsquo;s first European Cup win, says A Staff Reporter  The contest is open to individuals in the age group of 15 to 25 and   will be hosted on 
